headlines.description: — Alex Sarr scored 24 points and had seven rebounds to lead the Washington Wizards to a 119-114 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Wednesday night that snapped a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards use a big opening quarter to never trail in 119-114 victory over 76ers

headlines.description: — Orlando Robinson had 23 points on 10-of-14 shooting and added 12 rebounds to help the Toronto Raptors rout the Brooklyn Nets 116-86 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Orlando Robinson scores 23 points in the Raptors' 116-86 victory over the Nets

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had a buzzer-beating tip-in to cap a 10-point fourth quarter, Luka Doncic scored 34 points and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Indiana Pacers 120-119 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James beats buzzer with tip to lift Lakers past Pacers and keep record streak alive

events.name: LA Clippers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — James Harden had 29 points, six rebounds and six assists, Kawhi Leonard scored 27 points and the Los Angeles Clippers prevented the New York Knicks from clinching a playoff berth with a 126-113 victory Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers prevent Knicks from clinching a playoff spot with 126-113 victory

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 39 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists in his first game back in nearly two weeks to lead the Denver Nuggets to a 127-117 victory against the Milwaukee Bucks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic gets a triple-double in his return to lead Nuggets past Bucks 127-117

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis scored 30 points, Jaylen Brown added 24 and the Boston Celtics blew past the Phoenix Suns 132-102 on Wednesday night for their seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis scores 30 points, Celtics rout Suns 132-102 for 7th straight victory
